<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-591-610  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 591 610.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  June 11 1990 n372 p3(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Dot-matrix vendors slug it out.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gillooly, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Manufacturers of dot-matrix printers are in the midst of acut-throat pricing battle to retain market share.andP;  Analysts saythe dot-matrix market reached its peak in 1989 with a total of 5.2million units sold in the US.andP;  Totals for 1990 are forecast to beapproximately 5.1 million.andP;  Most manufacturers have cut prices inresponse to pressures from low price leaders such as Okidata.andO;Most vendors now have 24-pin printers available for under $500.andO;With margins shrinking, many vendors are now looking attransferring resources away from the dot-matrix market and intothe non-impact printer arena.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Dot-Matrix PrintersMarket AnalysisPriceIndustry AnalysisCompetitionMarketing Strategy.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Pricing patterns, 24-pin dot-matrix printers. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>